D.q[6143] = "So what about those souls I asked you for?";
D.q[4848] = "";
D.q[7118] = "";
D.q[6141] = "So what about those souls I asked you for?";
D.q[4849] = "";
D.q[7119] = "";
D.q[1931] = "I heard that Enutrofs discovered some tunnels under the city. I think something fishy is going on down there.";
D.q[5288] = "";
D.q[7063] = "The following stones...";
D.q[7117] = "";
D.q[5560] = "Don\'t you have anything better to do than to come here spouting this drivel?";
D.q[6137] = "So what about those souls I asked you for?";
D.q[7064] = "The following stones...";
D.q[5563] = "Hello! Thanks to me, Bonta will no longer face starvation. I wonder whether I should add some Trool meat and maybe some Mumussel and chip cobs to make a menu rich in calories.";
D.q[7121] = "";
D.q[7120] = "";
D.q[2584] = "ZZZZzzzzzzzZZZZZZZ (he\'s sleeping).";
D.q[4857] = "I hope you\'re proud of yourself! Thanks to you a traitor managed to get his job back... and he won\'t be the last either!";
D.q[6326] = "I hope the facilities are modern enough for you. I\'m sick of having to dress up as a dustbin to go unnoticed and I\'m starting to attract stray Bow Meows.";
D.q[6135] = "So what about those souls I asked you for?";
D.q[2240] = "Zo what? What arre you waiting forr to brring zis wood to your masterr?";
D.q[1289] = "Drink friends, drink... long live Brakmar, long live Brakmar... Do I really have to say that?";
D.q[7122] = "";
D.q[5644] = "You\'re very kind, so kind that I\'m going to join you in Bonta. You could show me round too... I\'ve never been out of Astrub. That\'s so nice of you. I\'m going to add you to my list of friends so that when you come near, I can find you and talk to you. I\'ve a few things to do right now though, so I\'ll meet you over there as soon as I\'ve finished.";
D.q[4934] = "";
D.q[5580] = "I just can\'t betray Mawy like that. She taught me all I knew. I owe her so much.";
D.q[5659] = "I\'m happy to see that you\'re starting to get the hang of this. I\'ve to say that I didn\'t think you\'d get that old bag to talk so easily. I\'ll tell Kafra Keeper and he\'ll send some men along to collect the statue. As for you, I\'m going to make you a Follower of Pain to reward you for solving this difficult case.";
D.q[7130] = "";
D.q[1241] = "Hello, don\'t be afraid... I\'m a nice sorcerer you know. Most sorcerers aren\'t as bad as they say, really.";
D.q[4879] = "Zzz... Fiend, dirty brute... not nice... zzzz...";
D.q[6159] = "Thanks for the potatoes. I don\'t like it at all when I run out! I\'d love to have a Twiggy Shovel, then I could grow them myself.";
D.q[4865] = "";
D.q[4874] = "Zzz... inkeeper... horrible soup... REFUND... zzzz...";
D.q[6157] = "Wonderful! I never thought I\'d see the day, but you\'ve completed a quest worthy of a hero. And you\'ll have a reward worthy of a hero, young one.";
D.q[4444] = "Don\'t delay, I want her to disappear as soon as possible.";
D.q[4935] = "";
D.q[6163] = "I\'ve seen several and have had the chance to study them, uncovering some of their secrets. Sometimes it may seem they\'re unique, but this is not true. My research tells me that Dragons don\'t lay a single Dofus, but often entire bundles! Just one of these eggs gives birth to a real Dragon. As for the others, I don\'t know what becomes of them.";
D.q[4968] = "";
D.q[7131] = "";
D.q[5998] = "";
D.q[4503] = "How is your investigation coming along?";
D.q[4939] = "";
D.q[6174] = "Really? That changes everything. There are more Bontarians than Brakmarians at the moment and any new cannon fodder...I mean new recruit\'s more than welcome. Want to join our ranks?";
D.q[5862] = "";
D.q[6146] = "So what about those souls I asked you for?";
D.q[6268] = "Forget what I just said, I\'ve a job for you. I hope you have those five gold ingots, the mother-of-pearl and the Royal Gobball Slobber on you, otherwise you\'ll have to get some more.\nListen carefully. I really don\'t want to repeat myself. I hate that. In the Alchemists\' workshop in Brakmar, there\'s a secret passage behind the central trunk. You\'re going to go there and enchant Kain Dharyn\'s crystal. You won\'t be able do it alone, you\'ll need a Jewelmagus, a master alchemist and a master miner along with you. You\'ll also need to have a Harmony, a Gust Potion and Kobalite mixed with Royal Gobball Slobber.";
D.q[5683] = "You again. Do you have the ingredients this time at least? Just to show that you\'re not pulling my leg...";
D.q[6244] = "I see, sir has expensive tastes. Well, not to worry, I\'ve exactly what you need. The King of Borins Crown. It\'s a unique piece... three entire diamond mines were emptied to create it, an ocean was dried out and a forest cut down to smelt the metal. You want to see it?";
D.q[3804] = "I knew it. Wanna trade for this extremely rare item? ";
D.q[6273] = "I don\'t want any trouble with the Brakmar militia. I was told just what Oto Mustam was doing to the prisoners and it doesn\'t bear repeating. All the same, food must be put on the table and we\'ve kids to clothe. So... give me 2,000 Kamas and I\'ll put a halt to what I\'m doing.";
D.q[4941] = "";
D.q[5299] = "";
D.q[4836] = "*Questions Miss Yelliott*\n(...)\n*turns to you*\nNow that you have questioned the witness, do you believe that her testimony is trustworthy?";
D.q[1520] = "Are you sure? Whatever the means, is the absolute power the only thing you really want to obtain?";
D.q[6333] = "Thanks a million, that\'ll be handy for paying the deposit for my Bow Meows. I\'ve one copy of the Canine Training Technique left, take good care of it.";
D.q[5686] = "Greetings. Was Terra Cogita the Enutrof cooperative?";
D.q[4158] = "So, did you find all the supplies I need?";
D.q[4878] = "";
D.q[6164] = "I\'ve studied their form, texture, weight and balance, measuring all that can be measured, but I still cannot tell the difference between a Dofus that gives birth to a Dragon and a Dofus that holds something else. There is much that our rational minds don\'t know. The magic within these eggs is so great that it transcends even the most fundamental of our natural laws.";
D.q[1535] = "I knew my brothers wouldn\'t let me rot away in this filthy stinking prison.\nHurry, let\'s get out of here!";
D.q[6373] = "You\'re saying that the horn should be on Moon Island and yet you haven\'t even prepared Kokonuts for your next mission? Useless! Get out of my sight! I\'m surrounded by bungling amateurs and incompetent layabouts of all kinds!";
D.q[6382] = "If you haven\'t chosen youw path yet, it\'s because you know that light cannot satisfy youw desiwes. Dawkness tempts you but you\'re scawed of the unknown, that\'s nowmal. If you let youw dawk side take contwol, evewything will become easiew, twust me.";
D.q[2170] = "I knew you were no wimp! Let\'s move on to more serious matters.";
D.q[7148] = "";
D.q[4721] = "Let me think.\nI think I saw someone following him, but I can\'t be sure, and I don\'t think I\'d be able to describe him. There were a lot of people on the square at the time.";
D.q[6401] = "I remember you now! You released me from the clutches of the goblins. You\'re lucky, I once helped Xavier the Baker during one of Jon Lemon\'s funeral ceremonies. I\'ll note the recipe on paper. For flour, ask Shika Ingalsse. She provides us with it.";
D.q[7149] = "";
D.q[4221] = "For now, it seems to be feeling good in its peat bog but we still had to build protections around it to prevent accidents. From time to time, my colleagues go and check the size and smell of this creature. It looks quite evil but as it\'s a unique and outstanding creature, it\'s become a priceless subject for experiments.";
D.q[6411] = "You look like you\'ve just soiled yourself. Here, I wrote down the recipe on this piece of paper. Guard it with your life and don\'t talk to anyone about it or I\'ll kill you while you sleep.\nSince you\'re here, as you seem to be looking for old recipes, go interrogate my friend Nikos Monot, he knows a good one. Don\'t, however, listen to his stories as he\'s a little crazy. He told me stories about the water stretching as far as the eye could see to the west of the Cania Plains and that boats can travel on it for months. Everyone knows that the Cania Plains stretch into infinity.";
D.q[4830] = "";
D.q[7150] = "";
D.q[6500] = "Haha! You\'re even dumber than you look. I just have to snap my fingers and the entire Brakmar militia will come looking for me. So do you feel like taking on forty armed guards at once? No? Well I suggest you learn some manners then. Please and thank you\'re so old-fashioned... how about 10,000 Kamas or so to lighten the atmosphere?";
D.q[5863] = "I know that Shush sent you because you are competent. So where\'s the key to Hotomani?";
D.q[2472] = "Play, play and play again... I\'m crazy about playing...";
D.q[2573] = "I know that one of them is riving in the evir forest. Find her and she\'r ter you which Dofus she\'s watching... Meeting her wir change you for ever. Come back to me when you\'ve discovered the secret of Pandara!";
D.q[5029] = "";
D.q[6572] = "I know the Crackler Mountain mine, but it\'s too busy there and I really don\'t want to have a run in with a Dark Miner who\'ll steal my precious alloys.\nSettling down underneath Amakna Square is out of the question - I don\'t want to be stuck in a village surrounded by people. Just thinking about it makes me feel sick.\nThe Porco Mine? Well, it\'s out in the sticks, so yes, that could work.\nOk, that\'s it, I\'m going to move to the Porco Mine. In the meantime, bring me everything I need to forge the equipment for the militia. I\'ve made a list, follow it carefully.";
D.q[5310] = "";
D.q[7151] = "";
D.q[7152] = "";
D.q[6537] = "Well, you followed my orders, that\'s a good thing. You took advantage of the bitch and led her to believe she was safe and then you killed her. Rather vile behaviour, and I like it. In truth, it was a test. It was a double that you killed while the real Petra came to me to report on your actions. Continue like that and you\'ll go far, I love my right hand men to be like you. Not too stupid but disciplined, that\'s exactly what I need for my most important tasks, if you\'re fit enough, of course.\nI\'d advise you not to approach Petra again, though, for whatever reason. Do I make myself understood? If you so much as lay a finger on her, or worse, think about her, I\'ll force you to swallow a live Miremop.";
D.q[6550] = "Congratulations, we undid the Brakmarians\' plan with your help, but I\'m worried about something... their equipment is of such high quality. It\'s unacceptable. Are we not the most powerful city in the World of Twelve?\nHere\'s 2,000 Kamas for the job. You can leave for now, I\'ve a few words to say to Amayiro about this.";
D.q[7153] = "";
D.q[2541] = "I know vely little, my fliend, but enough to satisfy you. Bling a Pandapiler flask to my old fliend, the mastel of the village of Akwadala and I\'ll tell you evelything I know about the Dofus of Pandala.";
D.q[7154] = "";
D.q[943] = "Hick my friend! How are you fine hick today?\nYou want to know som\'thin\'? Hey, you want to know som\'thin\'?... Pooh, you\'ll find out anyway: Bonta is the most beautiful city, because you won\'t find this kind of beer in hick Braaakkkkmarrrrr... Want some? No. More for me.";
D.q[5705] = "How is your search for the Statue of Sumens going?";
D.q[5231] = "";
D.q[7155] = "";
D.q[5036] = "Ahh, wonderful. You did good finding this demon symbol. This will secure my reputation as a guru!\nLook, I\'m going to be generous for once and give you these potions.";
D.q[7156] = "";
D.q[6587] = "Bwork magic makes use of the elements, and for this reason, it\'s very similar to the magic used by the Twelve gods. The basic difference lies in its use more than in its effects. When a Bwork mage uses magic, he will never be able to control it fully, he recites formulae that have the desired effect, but in a very imprecise way.\nA very few Bworks, usually the most intelligent, don\'t stop at learning the formulae by heart, but go on to perfect their mastery of the elements. They create spells and bewitchments with many different effects. Often these incantations are devastating.";
D.q[5041] = "Imbecile, IDIOT! How could you choose the WORST SYMBOL OF ALL!!??\nIf you weren\'t so useful to me, I\'d throw you to the dogs!";
D.q[1638] = "You\'re hardened enough to cope alone from now on. No need for you to go back inside.";
D.q[6592] = "What\'s wrong? Don\'t you smell that... smell that hangs in the air. The gods gave me an overdeveloped sense of smell, and it\'s ruining my life. I can\'t blame the people around me - it\'s not their fault... but I can\'t leave either, because Bworknroll would proclaim himself Bwork Archmage. The gods laid a curse on me, and I still don\'t know why. What can I do...";
D.q[4957] = "";
D.q[2565] = "I know you\'ve come a long way. Dark Vlad went mad a long time ago... No one can come out unchanged of this encounter: your spirit\'s stronger now!";
D.q[2574] = "I know whele you come flom my fwiend. Dark Vlad enteled the mist of madness a long time ago... No one can walk away fwom this encountel unchanged. Now your spilit\'s stlonger!\nYou asked him the question and he answeled.... Dark Vlad gualds the Emewald Dofus!";
D.q[4963] = "";
D.q[3218] = "True... We were talking about this maze...\nIf you want to enter the slab room, you\'ll need a special key that might have to put together from Lousy Pig remains.\nOnce in the slab room, you can choose your destination room by stepping on the right slab. Then, you\'ll have to work your way to the Dragon Pig Den! However, I must warn you: You\'ll need another key to enter this den and you\'ll find it only with its owners, the terrible Porcos that you come across in this maze.";
D.q[3821] = "I know. I catch them, I kill them by the dozen, and one always comes scurrying back. You want to kill a few? Be my guest. I tell you, my cheese won\'t last long at this rate.";
D.q[2509] = "Some of us have been very nervous since new arrivals set foot on our ancestral island. Not all Pandawas obey the laws of Grandapan! Pandikazes, those rebels, are the worst! Incidentally, the seller who unloaded this hat on you might be one of them... And this mysterious illness infecting the Enutrofs of Astrub is not helping... Be careful...";
D.q[7508] = "I\'ve two different powers that can change your characteristics. Do you want to learn more about them?";
D.q[7533] = "Which Doploons do you want to exchange?";
D.q[7532] = "Which Doploons do you want to exchange?";
D.q[2785] = "Tsskk... now that big dolt\'s gone, we\'ve a chance of gettin outta here...";
D.q[5630] = "Take my advice: find a Gobball set and never let it go.";
D.q[4964] = "";
D.q[7538] = "Which Doploons do you want to exchange?";
D.q[7536] = "Which Doploons do you want to exchange?";
D.q[7535] = "Which Doploons do you want to exchange?";
D.q[7537] = "Which Doploons do you want to exchange?";
D.q[2905] = "Nice one, mercenary!";
D.q[1092] = "Here, I\'ll lend it to you, but don\'t forget to give it back to me...Burrrp, oh, I\'m not feeling very well. A beer could help me get through this hard time. Come back any time my friend...Yoooo!";
D.q[5142] = "Ture Inge is interrogating Rogue Inkgo to try and get some info out of him.";
D.q[7444] = "";
D.q[7248] = "";
D.q[37] = "Hi, I\'m Abely Bobeule, the renowned woodcarver. When it comes to sculpting Wands, Bows and Staffs, my talent is beyond compare.";
D.q[5636] = "I learn lots of things just listening to people talking by the Zaap. They talk about their exploits, how they\'ve vanquished mythical creatures or discovered immense riches. They prance around with all their super duper equipment, sometimes attack people, but always in good spirit. The craziest thing is their respect for other folk. Have I told you already about their respect for other folk? No? Well let me tell you how much they respect other folk.";
D.q[2957] = "Pnj(163) et Message(2950)";
D.q[87] = "Hi! My name is Charlotte but for some reason everybody calls me Charlot. Help me to understand why by bringing me written proof and, I\'ll give you a nice reward.\nBy the way, I\'m looking for Wheat Flour to make some brioches, too. I\'ll give you a Flax String for one unit of Wheat Flour.";
D.q[91] = "Hello, my name is Elya Wood, and I need to eat Mushrooms in order to make my wings more colourful.  \nIf you bring me one, I\'ll give you my Wand Slasher which will allow you to carve wands, provided you have learnt the appropriate trade, of course.";
D.q[1697] = "I love making fairyworks, I know a fairywork maker in Bonta who sells at a reduced price. But the colourful resources required to craft them are hard to find...";
D.q[4996] = "";
D.q[176] = "Hmmm... #1, Oto Mustam\'s lapdog. What do you want, vile Brakmarian?";
D.q[7358] = "";
D.q[6654] = "";
D.q[185] = "The Rogues are the cruellest, most vile beings, they\'re feared by all in Amakna. I\'ve been a member of this Brotherhood for many years, and I\'ve no regrets whatsoever. Thanks to them, I\'ve gained power and respect.";
D.q[4102] = "I love pets too much to kill them and feed their corpses to my favourite dragoone. I prefer my pets alive, but you know, that\'s how Nature is, she can be cruel as well as kind. However, if you bring me any pet ghost and an Eniripsa powder, I\'ll take them off your hands and give you back a perfectly healthy new pet!\nHowever, as healthy as it might be, it will be very young, and so you\'ll have to start training it all over again.";
D.q[243] = "Hello there, my name is Lanseuf, I\'m from Troille. Let me tell you something before you go any further. Behind that little copse there, see, there\'s a worrying network of plant life, and I\'m its guardian. Yes, you guessed it, it\'s a labyrinth. I tell you, young one, I\'ve lost count of how many curious souls strayed in there looking for the treasure it\'s supposed to hide in its planty depths. All I can say is nearly the same number never came out again.";
D.q[5715] = "You again. Is the Statue of Sumens in the safe place you know about?";
D.q[5257] = "I made a list. Find some warriors and capture these territories. Could you go and take care of it now?";
D.q[309] = "Since I\'ve gained the trust of my clients, I can make them believe anything. For instance, at the moment I sell them coats made of mouse hair and mouse skin, telling them it\'s very fashionable. Well, I now have so many orders I don\'t even know if I\'ve got enough mouse hair...";
D.q[5724] = "Greetings. What good news do you bring?";
D.q[3549] = "I miss wearing my uniform. What fun it was roaming aimlessly with my mates... ";
D.q[3143] = "I must admit, you know how to fight. Next time, I won\'t let you win and you\'ll see what an Eniripsa Master like me can do.";
D.q[6462] = "Ahaahahaha! What a great deal! Here! take your key, mug!";
D.q[3437] = "I must go to the market. Adventurers always have such nice things to sell.";
D.q[350] = "In order to absorb all the vibrations in a more efficient way, the shaft of my axe needs to be restored with Treechnid Wood. You\'ll find some if you kill some of the Treechnids that doze near the Guilty Trees. Some of them hide between Farle and Shika Ingalsse\'s farm and the Lake of Amakna.\n\nBring me 10 Treechnid Roots and 10 Treechnid Barks and I\'ll give you a good axe in exchange.";
D.q[1036] = "You can be sure that Musa the Wolf Shooter is the best hunter in all Amakna. No thing or beast can resist me.";
D.q[386] = "Hi #1, I\'m Otomai\'s assistant. He\'s one of the few enchanters in Amakna.\nI help him create charms for weapons, but also potions and magic scrolls.\nWhat can I do for you ?";
D.q[5387] = "";
D.q[7359] = "";
D.q[3239] = "After several years spent within the castle, the survivors of the village decided to rebuild it next to the castle with the help of the Astrubians. It\'s what we now know as the village of Amakna. \nNowadays, only thrill-seekers and Dreggon-cutters dare to venture in this devastated village. You can come across Rogues and Brigands who come to pillage everything that\'s been left in houses or simply take refuge in a place where very few people dare to go...";
D.q[436] = "He\'s been waiting for years near the bridge to warn the potential adventurers about the danger that awaits them.\nYou know, he\'s responsible for the disaster which forced us to flee here and rebuild our village. \nIf you manage to help him, he will certainly give you his Old Dreggon Bone - it\'s got magic powers.\nIf you know how to use it correctly it will bestow great powers on amulets.";
D.q[7360] = "";
D.q[444] = "It\'s older than the oldest Enutrof, more deceitful than the most deceitful Rogue and more dangerous than a drunken Bwork Magus.\nYou shouldn\'t challenge it alone, it often goes out for a walk, with its whole army of Arachnees in the forests near the Southern Sawmill. It\'s always in search of new lumberjacks to devour.\nOne last thing, beware of its magic. It almost killed Brouce Boulgour the Lumberjack last winter.";
D.q[5698] = "Silver? I\'ve hidden tons of it.";
D.q[3946] = "I need all the ingredients otherwise I can\'t prepare your potion.";
D.q[1650] = "I need more details, I need to focus my divination on a chosen place before consulting my crystal ball.";
D.q[407] = "I need Elm wood to reinforce my mine and prevent it from collapsing. \nBut I\'m a poor Lumberjack. The last time I tried to cut down a tree, I walked on an old Treechnid root... It pursued me and laid siege to my mine for about ten days.\nIf you bring me 10 units of Elm woods, I\'ll give you a miner\'s pick.\nDon\'t hesitate to call on a Lumberjack if you don\'t want to lose too much time.";
D.q[6750] = "I need to think for a while. I\'ve no more use for you.";
D.q[1658] = "I can feel a great energy in the Hall of the Prism, the Dopple territory can be attacked for the moment.";
D.q[4078] = "Which spell do you want to unlearn?";
D.q[83] = "I never actually found out how to do it.";
D.q[1790] = "If you want to challenge a Dopple, you must make a donation to the Cra temple.\nIt will cost you a Small Twiggy Bow.";
D.q[562] = "Hi and welcome in Dofus.\nYou\'re in Tainela, the cradle of Amakna, the Eternal province of Dofus. In that place, you\'ll learn the rudiments that must know every new adventurer.\nAfter that initiation, you\'ll be able to search for the precious Dofus, these Dragons eggs with prodigious powers, all over the country.";
D.q[4453] = "50,000 Kamas? For that much money, I\'ll come and join you! Let me know when you can escort me there.";
D.q[1809] = "If you want to challenge a Dopple, you must make a donation to the Enutrof temple.\nIt will cost you Bronze.";
D.q[3852] = "I once found one nestled in the darkest depths of a dungeon! It was sparkling, shining. I couldn\'t take my eyes off that glowing vision. But a dirty rival adventurer stormed into the place and snatched it from under my nose. I gave him a kick in the Dofus, but to no avail... Ohh, I missed the opportunity of a lifetime.";
D.q[4082] = "Which spell do you want to unlearn?";
D.q[4069] = "I once tried to gather all the living creatures known to date in one place on this island.\nUnfortunately, the aggressive instinct of some of those creatures caused me to fail. I never managed to make them live together in a restricted space or acclimatise all of them to this island habitat.";
D.q[5006] = "Hello, do you know what would make me really happy?\nThe 638 Dwarf Bus. With that broom I could fly over pretty little Bonta and blow it up.";
D.q[2925] = "Greetings, may the light follow your every step. \nWhat can I do for you?";
D.q[3364] = "I own a powerful family relic. We usually pass it on from father to son, generation after generation. Failing that, the family tradition allows it to be passed down to a powerful warrior. I\'m not convinced you\'re worthy!";
D.q[4061] = "Which spell do you want to unlearn?";
D.q[1808] = "If you want to challenge a Dopple, you must make a donation to the Enutrof temple.\nIt will cost you a Kriptonit.";
D.q[7504] = "";
D.q[668] = "According to the legend, you must avoid this forest at all costs. It says that the dark, blood-tinged mystery it holds will arouse fears you didn\'t even know you had. But I don\'t believe the stories, this forest is a delight of magic to me, with charming smells and fairy sounds. I fathomed its mystery a long time ago but I can\'t say anything. The same way I wouldn\'t stand up for anyone. However, I can sell you a book that recounts the legend of the forest.";
D.q[4313] = "";
D.q[4063] = "Which spell do you want to unlearn?";
D.q[5154] = "";
D.q[728] = "I\'ve 4 boxes of knives to transport to the outpost of Bonta, in the South. \nBe careful, each of them weighs around 500 pods. You\'ll have to make several trips.";
D.q[4758] = "I saw you in a vision... saw you coming to me for advice.";
D.q[4080] = "Which spell do you want to unlearn?";
D.q[7505] = "";
D.q[628] = "I really like this island. I just can\'t get enough of it. Listening to the lapping of water under the bridge is one of my favourite activities... or inactivities to be precise. I like picking flowers too...";
D.q[743] = "You\'ll have to carry out a reconnaissance mission. You\'ll explore the cemetery of the Tortured eastward of Brakmar. Tell me when You\'re ready to go.";
D.q[4760] = "Ah yes, have you got what I asked you for?";
D.q[2738] = "Did you know Simgood the sailorman wanted to retire? I can\'t believe it! But you can\'t teach an old Pandawa new drinks, as we say. It\'s probably a trick to steal my Fishing Points... I\'m sure this old Sea Boowolf is plotting something. Those Madrestam folk can\'t be trusted!";
D.q[5437] = "";
D.q[758] = "Bring me 100 headbands. It\'s for an elite troop going north to regions you\'d better not visit for the moment.";
D.q[828] = "Bring me the pulp of Crushed Blop Flowers. Then I\'ll just have to add some Scurvion poison to it to kill Amayiro\'s Tabi.\nThe idiot only feeds his Tabi with this mixture. It should be easy to have one of my agents make the Tabi swallow it.";
D.q[812] = "Chafers are great for cannon fodder in the wars against Bonta... but I\'d be lying if I said they were good fighters. They make the enemy tired though, which is nice.\nAnyway, fight against Mak so that I can see how skilful you\'re when it comes to confronting a chafer. If you lose against this bag of bones, I\'ll know exactly what I\'m dealing with.";
D.q[6933] = "That sounds like a load of blarney. It\'s not?\nOh, okay then. You see, I don\'t like competition much, so if I discover that you\'re lying, I\'ll stick a shovel where the sun don\'t shine, got it?";
D.q[5489] = "I saw you challenge Ougaa. You could almost pass for one of my students if you knew how to dress a little better. It hurts my eyes just looking at you. Talk about colour-clash...";
D.q[4762] = "Hmm, it\'s a pity. Well, too bad... bring back Oto\'s blade.";
D.q[835] = "Raahh, I\'m really angry. The 3 heads got wind of my wealth and they came to strip me off. I\'m angry and hungry! Do you know what we\'re having for lunch? Boiled potatoes and crow-belly?\nWell, now you know, so you can be in charge of peeling the spuds. Ask the cook what to do, he might need some more crows. If so, find them for him. Hurry up!";
D.q[2929] = "I see you know about the existence of elemental tonics that only great Pandawushu masters can make! \nAs the Fire Pandawushu master, I can provide you with a flame which will revive your warrior soul for your next fights...";
D.q[202] = "You can\'t bluff an Ecaflip, you should know that. You don\'t have what I asked you for...";
D.q[6934] = "I used to be a great treasure hunter, but one day I came face to face with a dragon! Yes, a dragon, I assure you.\nWe chatted for hours and he gave me his treasure, and so, covered in wealth, I found myself a lovely wife and settled here.\nMy adorable Annapelle raises Dragoturkeys and I hunt them to make dishes that I then sell to wholesale buyers. And yes, I\'m the expert on meals using Dragoturkey meat. Unfortunately you\'re too late, I just delivered the last crates, but you can place an order if you want, the quote will only cost you 5,000 Kamas.\nOne last bit of advice, avoid going down in the basement, that\'s where I cut slaughter and butcher the Dragoturkeys.";
D.q[1805] = "If you want to challenge a Dopple, you must make a donation to the Sacrier temple.\nIt will cost you Scurvion Blood.";
D.q[978] = "Hi, I\'m Anik Mech. My uncle Riorraw is a great inventor. He\'s actually working on a machine which will enable us to get from place to place as quickly as a Tabi!";
D.q[991] = "Hi! You\'re at the south outpost of Bonta, how can I help you?";
D.q[1081] = "Of course I\'ll take it! And that drunkard Mili Taver will listen to me next time. He\'s always way too drunk when I see him...";
D.q[5438] = "";
D.q[5888] = "I see you\'re holding a piece of paper in your hand. Is the report on the meeting between Maimane and Silvosse?";
D.q[4763] = "Not too difficult, huh? The next one will be a little more... less easy.";
D.q[5446] = "";
D.q[5662] = "I see you\'ve brought me some gifts. To repay your kindness, I\'ll help you. Now what were you saying again?\nThe Statue of Sumens, hmm, that sounds familiar. I\'ve it! My old friend Terra Cogita told me about them once. Her sister Terra Bitya knew where they were, but she died a few years ago. Her brother buried her near the bridge over the river Kawaii.";
D.q[1303] = "Well, let\'s make a deal. You\'ll have to kill someone for me, for 10,000 Kamas. A certain Rimaraf. He lives in the South-West of the city. He\'s a high-ranking militiaman, not a bad guy but he overshadows me. I\'d like you to break into his house and bring him a poisoned dessert. \nHe has a weakness for cakes, so he will inevitably eat this poisoned Rasputin Cake! \nYou\'ll have to ask a baker to make you this cake plus find the poison.";
D.q[1325] = "Oh! That Oto is really a nasty piece of work. He\'s cruel. I can\'t stand the demons of Brakmar as a rule, but all the same, I respect anyone with a sense of honour. Only a few demons still respect the ancient code. I can understand your situation, if you want to keep your honour intact, I can lie about the fact that you brought me these ears.";
D.q[5440] = "";
D.q[1345] = "You want to play Rock, Paper, Scissors with me? ME? You cheeky monkey, don\'t you know I\'m the champion of Amakna? Anyhow, I only play for money... okay?\nWe\'ll play three rounds, 10 Kamas a round... and you can stop whenever you want..\nYou must win the 3 rounds to win the game.";
D.q[1338] = "You\'re lucky, I\'ve a disenchantment potion right here.\nNow Colonel, there you go, you look much better.";
D.q[926] = "I see, him again...I\'ll deal with it. It won\'t be long! Thanks and don\'t hesitate to come back again.";
D.q[7163] = "";
D.q[1327] = "I see, you\'re not really different. Do as you wish.";
D.q[7164] = "";
D.q[1447] = "OK, well done! I hope I\'ll never hear from those scumbags again...\nI\'ll give this title deed to Danathor so that he can see to it.";
D.q[1454] = "Phew! That\'s better. I forgive you. It\'s true that he\'s precocious... just like his dad. Anyway. We\'re out of firewood...and guess what? It\'s up to you! Bring us 10 Treechnid barks. Here, take this note as a reminder... You don\'t want to forget the order again, do you?";
D.q[6366] = "I see. The Bontarians have been playing us for fools. You were looking for their ship and all along they were transporting their equipment by land. That makes sense given what we\'ve been hearing lately.";
D.q[7165] = "";
D.q[1654] = "The territory of the Dopples, hmmm, it\'s a place overflowing with Magic. The creatures that live there can take on the appearance of anything they see.\n*Polishes her crystal ball*\nI can see frequent confusion in alignments there, for the moment\nBonta troops have taken control of the area.";
D.q[7166] = "";
D.q[5748] = "I was almost shocked that nobody came to bother me for five whole minutes. What do you want this time?";
D.q[2745] = "I see... Let me tell you the stoly of the Callot Dofus. When the Wa Wabbit kicked us out of oul island, he splead the lumol saying he had a Dofus. This way he attlacted many adventulels he could easily despoil thanks to his gleat powels. This enteltaining activity made the Wa lich and happy.";
D.q[7167] = "";
D.q[2197] = "I still need a blue larva skin. \nGo have a look round the Northern gate of Astrub, that\'s where all the best larvae hang out.";
D.q[7168] = "";
D.q[7169] = "";
D.q[3916] = "I think I heard people talk about a prince coming from the far away land of Wa. I had never heard about this country before and no, I don\'t know where you can find him.";
D.q[5147] = "What? Don\'t take that holier-than-thou attitude when you look at me, it doesn\'t suit your terrible dress sense.";
D.q[5750] = "My Piwis are hungry, have you brought the feed I asked you for?";
D.q[7170] = "";
D.q[2066] = "You see, I can\'t leave my little girl alone while I\'m away. And she can\'t come with me either, she\'d only disturb everyone, including me! I\'ve a favour to ask you. Can you look after her for a few minutes. I won\'t be long...";
D.q[2095] = "Well, well...that\'s a special girl, and we can see who she\'s taking after. I\'ve one last favour to ask you. With all this fuss, some of our Gobballs have escaped. Some got lost near the underpasses.";
D.q[5207] = "";
D.q[7172] = "";
D.q[7171] = "";
D.q[7381] = "";
D.q[7174] = "";
D.q[7173] = "";
D.q[6311] = "*Hic* I ain\'t for sale. Ahh wait no, the bottle\'s empty.";
D.q[2422] = "The miner extracts the metal used by jewellers and blacksmiths as raw material. Some of the stones they find will also have magical value. From time to time, miners uncover valuable diamonds and the like - a rare occurrence, but it does happen. The mines themselves are few and far between and violent turf wars are not uncommon!";
D.q[7382] = "";
D.q[4769] = "So? What was the result?";
D.q[5161] = "";
D.q[2439] = "The baker makes his fine breads according to safely guarded traditions. Bread is perfect for a quick snack while you\'re roaming the world on important quests. The final product depends first and foremost, however, on flour, the raw material of any bread. Rumour has it that eating it regularly makes you stronger.";
D.q[5292] = "";
D.q[2709] = "A secret meeting is being held at this very moment in Aerdala. We don\'t know anything about what\'s going on over there... But we do know one thing: it\'s about the Dofus. The wise Lenald wishes to send you over there, as it\'s difficult to trust any of us at the moment, since Pandikazes are everywhere. But Lenald really thinks he can trust you. Be careful: many adventurers were given a cold welcome in Aerdala! Some say they\'re allied to the rebel Pandawas - those who sabotaged all the access roads of the island. You must infiltrate the enemy clan and report to us as much information as you can. Go see the wise... if you come back alive.";
D.q[2789] = "Well done. Let\'s get out of here! Now we split to confuse the issue. Good luck!";
D.q[2836] = "Greetings #1, I haven\'t seen you for a while! I see you\'ve become more discreet since our last meeting!\nWhat can I do for you?";
D.q[5367] = "";
D.q[2937] = "Haha, you\'re a true tunneller! I\'ll stop bugging you now. I\'ve enough data to try to find a theory and draw up the map of what you\'ve explored.... It might be my first bestseller!\n\nThere are still heaps of mysterious tunnels described in this book... in the Dark Smith Dungeon, in Sufokia... Come back and visit in a while... I might still need your help to explore all this!";
D.q[5164] = "";
D.q[5273] = "";
D.q[5396] = "";
D.q[5433] = "";
D.q[3114] = "Poor boy, he doesn\'t want to leave the jail even though King Allister pardoned him. He stole a whole convoy of potatoes fwom Wabbit Island.";
D.q[5186] = "";
D.q[3280] = "Silvosse seems to be with you... You\'re cured! The curse is coming out of you...\nWhat a pity! You were such a nice Treechnid!\n\nIf I were you, I wouldn\'t waste my time and I\'d try to get out of this dungeon while I still can.";
D.q[5444] = "";
D.q[4631] = "Find out more about Elturt, it\'s the only way of discovering his weak spot.";
D.q[5447] = "At the heart of the Nauseating Swamps is a sanctuary where the souls of dead pets gather. My ancestor Oshima has taken up residence there and he could bring your dead pet back to life.";
D.q[5478] = "";
D.q[5497] = "";
D.q[2289] = "I think Osamodas masters know a lot about these creatures. I don\'t know any masters personally, though...";
D.q[5492] = "Good day.\nTo strengthen the links between Pandawas and the other races of the World of Twelve, the goddess Pandawa has decided that newly incarnated souls should now appear at the foot of the recently erected statue in the city of Astrub. This is good news, don\'t you think?";
D.q[6859] = "";
D.q[3337] = "I\'m glad to see you my good friend! I knew we would work together again. Perhaps we can become partners, you and I. You can wander about the countryside, as I know you like to, and I, I\'ll create all sorts of things... Yes, wandering around the countryside... I know you like that! Yes, well, here is the list. I can\'t wait for you to return... I... I miss you already... I should stop... okay. Farewell, friend.";
D.q[7383] = "";
D.q[5165] = "";
D.q[4557] = "Hello my friend. What\'s brought you to Sufokia?";
D.q[6862] = "";
D.q[3141] = "I think that if the four sisters agree to lent you their brooch, it\'s because they trust you and you deserve to go through this door! Borrow their brooches and come back see me if you dare!";
D.q[7384] = "";
D.q[6748] = "I think it\'s the calm before the storm. I hope there won\'t be too many bandits.";
D.q[1527] = "I think it was the last wave. Heh heh heh, these Bontarians are nothing but a bunch of idiots.";
D.q[4584] = "Hello, how\'s your research into Elturt going?";
D.q[6863] = "";
D.q[3440] = "Children? No, I haven\'t seen any children for a long time. And yet, I love children, I love them a lot...";
D.q[3453] = "What\'s this strange dish... hmm, it\'s quite tasty... *crunch*, *yummm*, *slurp*, *buuuuuuuuuuurp*, delissshious! I haven\'t eaten that well since ... well, I can\'t even remember eating something that delicious in my whole life. I\'ll keep my promise but I don\'t want to see them around here ever again.";
D.q[6864] = "";
D.q[5166] = "";
D.q[5712] = "...";
D.q[6865] = "";
D.q[6866] = "";
D.q[1474] = "I told you we would be 10 for dinner tonight. So go get at least 10 carcasses! Right now!";
D.q[555] = "I understand, dear guest, but unfortunately I must disappoint you this time. Our agency has always committed itself to clarity and precision, just like our slogan says. We just can\'t let you go. But I can offer you an alternative...";
D.q[7385] = "";
D.q[7386] = "";
D.q[6867] = "";
D.q[4826] = "Don\'t forget our little agreement... Kit Dingaround IS guilty.";
D.q[7388] = "";
D.q[3454] = "Hey! What are you doing in my mine kid?\nAll the mines are mine! Haha!\nFor 50 Kamas, I can help you get out of this place. Just jump in the wagon. I\'ll give it a push and ride with you to the next mine.\nSometimes things can go wrong... if we end up in the wrong place, don\'t worry, I\'ll take care of you!\nDark Miners sometimes attack us, too. If you have friends, I\'d advise you to bring them along... You never know...";
D.q[7387] = "";
D.q[7390] = "";
D.q[351] = "I urgently need a Staff made of Treechnid Roots for my friend Farle Ingalsse who needs it to herd his Gobball Flocks... If you could call on a good Staff Carver who can make you one, and if you could bring it back to me, I\'ll give you a very rare resource: a Worked Sap of Treechnid.";
D.q[5619] = "Hahaha, you think we\'re going to start talking? We know all of Bonta\'s methods of interrogation and we\'re not going to tell you a thing. Why don\'t you go try and get some information out of your mother.";
D.q[3464] = "Brewing Bwork Beer or breeding Bworks... Which job will bring me the most Kamas with the least effort?";
D.q[7389] = "";
D.q[4483] = "I want you to intercept the weapons convoy before it reaches the Imp village, so what are you still doing here?\nIf you\'re here to tell me you have the booty, I already told you to bring it to Stampitor on the upper floor.";
D.q[7391] = "";
D.q[5351] = "I want you to find out about Divad Dleifrepok for me. I think he might be hiding something from me. Follow him discreetly and question him when the time comes. Be careful... and remember he\'s a first class illusionist.";
D.q[6335] = "I want to protect my buildings from Whitish Fangs too! By Djaul, you\'d better hurry before you\'re turned into Bow Wow biscuits.";
D.q[7392] = "";
D.q[1509] = "I wanted to meet you, young disciple of Oto Mustam. You\'ve performed quite a few astonishing feats for Brakmar lately. And it\'s inscribed in the darkness that it won\'t stop here.\nBut you don\'t know EVERYTHING about Brakmar just yet. This vision could change the way you see Brakmar.\nDo you want to hear it ?";
D.q[1390] = "I was surprised by a Bontarian and got knocked out. I couldn\'t see his face because of the darkness, what a shame... by Djaul! We can see his tracks going Westward. I hope he hasn\'t gone too far.";
D.q[1058] = "I warned you, you must know when to stop! \nAnyway I\'m in a good mood today. So just try again.";
D.q[4817] = "I was wondering about this famous horn of Bonta. If it\'s so powerful, why haven\'t they attacked yet? I think they\'re hiding something. Go and find Finche Aticus, the spy in Bonta, and ask him if he has any news.";
D.q[2036] = "I was waiting for you! You know, the hilt of a sword is of the utmost importance! Every year, many warriors die because their sword\'s hilt was not fitted correctly. You\'ll find the best ones here! It\'s been a family tradition for more than a hundred years. I advise you to take this one, it\'s powerful, delicate, made of Treechnid wood and set with a Dragoturkey feather. Try it and you\'ll see!";
D.q[4527] = "I was waiting. I\'ve another mission for you if you\'re interested. And let me tell you, I\'ll pay you better than Amayiro will ever do...";
D.q[3409] = "You can\'t to see the turnip pile for the turnips, step back from the canvas, child.";
D.q[4323] = "I was told that you were seen hanging around the streets... what do you have to say about that?";
D.q[167] = "I\'ll never exchange mine for all the tea in Sufokia, except for even more powerful decks. If you\'re looking for decks of cards, speak to people who like to play Tragic the Gardening, you\'ll certainly meet some of them as you travel. They may agree to exchange some cards with you.";
D.q[761] = "I won\'t have any mission to give you for a little while #1. Come back for the next update of our staff...";
D.q[5025] = "You did a great job and your help is very precious to me. Go have a break and come back to see me soon, I might have more jobs for you a little later.";
D.q[7177] = "";
D.q[7178] = "";
D.q[6060] = "I wonder where Sumens got to. We had planned to head off to the Cania Plains to drink our troubles away... he must have started without me.";
D.q[4829] = "I maintain that there\'s no reason for me to be here. I have nothing to do with it. I\'m an honest Sram.";
D.q[2091] = "I\'d like to teach her the art of magic. But, you see, I don\'t really have the time. I think you would make a great teacher. Teach her everything you know, it will be very good training for her, won\'t it Allisteria? *She doesn\'t answer*";
D.q[6869] = "";
D.q[4855] = "I knew I could count on you. Bonta doesn\'t stand for traitors, you did as you had to do.\nHere, take this for your trouble.";
D.q[7179] = "";
D.q[6870] = "";
D.q[3594] = "I\'d be happy to help you find some work, but you can earn a lot more Kamas down in Amakna. It might be time for you to leave Incarnam.";
D.q[4218] = "I wrote several books on this island and I read many books on this lost civilization. Unfortunately, we can no longer find them in libraries. Some authorities believe that books are dangerous, questioning the power of some gods and trying to explain things that shouldn\'t be known.";
D.q[7180] = "";
D.q[5311] = "If you like me have seen enough of the segregation that\'s you again?!\nIf you\'re coming to shut me up, my gang and I will make short work of you. Am I right, Fryar Truck";
D.q[2016] = "I\'d like to know what those Xelors get up to with this Epyss Grain. I don\'t know why it\'s so rare, they\'re the only ones who use the damn stuff! It\'s tasteless and, short of some magical encouragement, it\'s impossible to get a drop of oil out of it. I\'ll tell you one thing, though... this plant grows deep in the heart of a volcano not far from here... usually such an environment would make it highly volatile.";
D.q[6871] = "";
D.q[7181] = "";
D.q[2288] = "I\'d like to tell you... But afterwards, I\'d have to tie your nice little pink tongue in a knot so you wouldn\'t be able to tell anyone else...*a slightly unfriendly grin*";
D.q[4121] = "Ahem... I don\'t know... I... I don\'t know the answer to that question! You got me. I\'ve lost at my own game. I\'m a joke. I\'m even stupider than you. I didn\'t think it was possible. Please... Please don\'t tell anyone that you defeated the Death Bridge Keeper and his questions, I\'m begging you...\nI\'ll let you cross the bridge whenever you wish.";
D.q[6861] = "";
D.q[7182] = "";
D.q[3897] = "Good morning, faithful servant! I need your help. Can you do me a favour? you\'ll be rewarded for your efforts.";
D.q[6872] = "";
D.q[5633] = "I\'d watch out if I were you - you really shouldn\'t stray too far outside Astrub... it\'s far too dangerous.";
D.q[7183] = "";
D.q[7490] = "";
D.q[369] = "I\'ll give you a magic scroll for some ingredients.";
D.q[1247] = "Nice to meet you, what can I do for you? If you\'re looking for bread or brioches, you\'ve come to the right place!";
D.q[6264] = "I\'ll do what\'s necessary the next time a Bontarian comes round this way, but it\'ll cost you 2,000 Kamas.";
D.q[6873] = "";
D.q[4810] = "I\'ll do it quickly. Oto doesn\'t like people taking up too much of his time - once you have the leaves, bring them to me so I can modify them too.";
D.q[7491] = "";
D.q[7255] = "";
D.q[4152] = "That\'s perfect! I\'ll be able to mix all these flours and with a bit of luck, no one will ever notice.";
D.q[5416] = "";
D.q[6874] = "";
D.q[7176] = "";
D.q[4893] = "Those cursed Brakmarians have benefited from our domestic concerns to vandalise our workshops and steal several magic items. Go and see Ebru Of El in the Tower of Bonta, he could do with your help.";
D.q[752] = "I\'ll soon need you again. Keep on practicing to be in shape when the time comes.";
D.q[4823] = "";
D.q[4430] = "I\'ll take a closer look at that, there\'s no point in staying around here. Take a look in Sufokia and see if I\'m there.";
D.q[7186] = "";
D.q[6875] = "";
D.q[6876] = "";
D.q[4169] = "I\'m determined to have the fastest tamed Scaraleaves but for that I\'d need to be able to ride them without slowing them down.\nThat\'s why I\'d need a specific equipment and not this stupid helmet and wooden pair of wings which only enable me to crush down if I fall off my Scaraleaf and uselessly weigh down my means of transport.\nI need an improved pilot helmet and cape. Do you think you could get this for me? You\'ll probably need to find an experienced tailor.";
D.q[4776] = "I want to know how that witness knew about a confidential document in Kit Dingaround\'s bag.";
D.q[7187] = "";
D.q[7188] = "";
D.q[4181] = "Well, you\'re one of the most courageous adventurers I\'ve ever met. I haven\'t seen anyone killing creatures that fierce in such a short time for ages. \nI\'ll talk to Otomai next time I\'ll see him. He\'ll certainly be happy to know that you helped one of his oldest friends.";
D.q[7256] = "";
D.q[4253] = "I\'ll wait for you then.";
D.q[5424] = "";
D.q[6877] = "";
D.q[7189] = "";
D.q[4833] = "I really can\'t see what more I can add to my statement... but I suppose that\'s the procedure.";
D.q[7257] = "";
D.q[4220] = "This giant creature became really fat and its acid and putrid excrements modified part of the island\'s ecosystem. Plants and all sorts of living things are dying as a result. We\'re afraid that it could move and contaminate the rest of the island. The oil slick it could create would be a disaster for our society.";
D.q[4227] = "Tremble, mortals. This monster existed before the island, it\'s the island. None can equal its power - Otomai with his fancy spells will not be the first. I\'ve heard of his terrible creation and I don\'t believe a word.";
D.q[6878] = "";
D.q[2030] = "I\'m a bit short on potions lately, a lot of people ask me for them... ahem! Anyway, what can I do for you?";
D.q[7190] = "";
D.q[4860] = "I\'m happy with the way things have gone. Kit really owes you one. Here, have this from him and me. I think you\'ve deserved it.";
D.q[5430] = "";
D.q[935] = "Hello, I\'m the owner of the Goldenring Jewellery. What can I do for you?";
D.q[1226] = "Hi there! How are you? I need a new wardrobe. The area is famous for its tailors such as Paro Cabanne, Laurent Saint-Yves, Caca Chonel... just to name a few...";
D.q[1313] = "I\'m bored stiff! I\'ve spent the whole night and day just staring at this jewellery. I can\'t remember the last time something happened. It\'s getting harder and harder to keep my eyes open.";
D.q[7492] = "";
D.q[1335] = "I\'m both exhausted and proud to have trashed Brakmar.\nMy men are celebrating our victory but I\'m going to get some sleep.";
D.q[7258] = "";
D.q[7191] = "";
D.q[3278] = "I\'m enthralled by your victory over the Soft Oak. That legendary creature has lived through tempests without being uprooted and autumns without losing a leaf...\n\nHow did a mere, incapable mortal like yourself manage to bring down such an imposing and powerful creature? Mother Nature really is surprising sometimes.";
D.q[7493] = "";
D.q[4556] = "";
D.q[7192] = "";
D.q[2649] = "I\'m getting ready and I\'ll be right there! Wait for me at the Dojo, you, blue Larva!";
D.q[363] = "I\'m getting ready for my fifth marriage. Some people never meet the one for them, but I\'ve met five, hey, I\'m lucky. My latest fiancé is very thoughtful, and rich. \nAnyway, I\'ve a small problem. I\'m making soup, to give him strength for our wedding night. Prespic Peak soup, to be exact and for this I need... well, Prespic Peaks. Bring me 80 of them and I\'ll give you a Small Strength Scroll in return.";
D.q[7494] = "";
D.q[7193] = "";
D.q[4239] = "I haven\'t got the time to repair your shield, but for the moment I\'ll give you this one in return for a broken shield of your own. I trade all models!";
D.q[7495] = "";
D.q[4392] = "Hmmm, a respected citizen of Bonta... whose name starts with X.\nYes, I might have some information... but you\'ll have to cross my hand with silver.\nThe temple\'s poison reserves are running low and I\'ve heard talk that Brakmar\'s are full to bursting point. I want you to bring me 10 Flasks of Brakmarian poison, and while you\'re there, you might as well borrow the client register in the alchemists\' workshop. \nI won\'t give you a word of information until I\'ve these items. Or a billion Kamas. \nDon\'t look at me like that, you must know someone in Brakmar who can help you out.";
D.q[7259] = "";
D.q[7496] = "";
D.q[7260] = "";
D.q[7194] = "";
D.q[7497] = "";
D.q[379] = "Hello! I\'m trying to make the biggest mushroom and seed fritter ever seen for the next feast in honour of Skippy The Guru. Could you help me look for some ingredients?\nIf you bring me 90 Mushrooms, 70 Sunflower seeds and 40 Hemp seeds, I\'ll give you a Great Wisdom Scroll in return.";
D.q[4532] = "You managed to get into their militia building and steal this document? Excellent. Let\'s see what\'s in here...\nWe don\'t have the time to read it carefully, every minute counts, so we have to act quickly. I\'m going to send men to the Cemetery of the Tortured and you\'ll go with them. When you\'ve finished with the Brakmarian patrol, come back and report to me. Now get out of here, you mustn\'t miss the patrol.";
D.q[7261] = "";
D.q[7498] = "";
D.q[1774] = "These scissors are yours from now on... Make good use of them.";
D.q[6594] = "Hello there. I organise unusual tracking expeditions with another member of my family. If you\'d like to come along with us some time, just let me know. I\'ll give you a target to catch and if you succeed I\'ll pay you for it. But I don\'t want any cowards or glory-hunters on my team. Any fights you fight will be fair and honourable. It\'s not always easy to find an even match, but the minute I\'ve something for you, I\'ll give you Seeker scrolls to help you. So, are you ready?";
D.q[7175] = "";
D.q[7262] = "";
D.q[3305] = "I\'m glad to see that young adventurers like you find time to go to the library now and then. You know, before, there were lots of shops and workshops here. But when the Dragoturkeys arrived, shopkeepers started breeding! It\'s a lot more profitable! The sale of all the shops financed the construction of all these paddocks and our wonderful library.";
D.q[7499] = "";
D.q[7184] = "";
D.q[2076] = "I\'m going to teach you how to shoot... with a bow. Nice reward, huh? But before we start, you need a bow! I don\'t have enough time, but Ticra will help you. You\'ll see, she\'s almost as handy as I\'m... almost...";
D.q[7500] = "";
